ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
Small expansions with few tiles or rules. 
Easy to put right into a game

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description: Medium amount of tiles, or adding new rules not present in Carcassonne previously

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
Huge expansions, either with many tiles, or more complex new rules.

Some of these even have their own expansions! How crazy.

There are some that only add tiles, without adding rules, as well.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds small wells to roads, granting extra points

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Wells - adds 12 Tiles.

Adds a new feature to roads, wells.

Grants 1 additional points on finished roads. 
( 2 per tile instead of 1. )
Grants 2 additonal points if the finished road has an inn.
( 3, instead of 1. )

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds a small forest to the start of the game, like with the River

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Little Forest (lite) - By Quevy - p2
ContainedObjects.Description:
The expansion itself does have additional rules, you can find a link to the .pdf on the workshop page.

The rules I wrote here were just a lite version, to add more geography to the start of the game, like the river does.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Little Forest (lite) - By Quevy - p1
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds 14 Tiles. 
Adds a forest to the start of the game.
Can be used alongside the river.

Place the 4-sided forest first.
Then draw the tiles, and place them to make a forest, but don't place any followers.
Finish the forest and start the game proper. ( Or even add the river, first. )

A Notecard with a summary of the rules is in each bag. 
Some expansions do however have more complex rules, and in those cases I reccomend reading the pdf at CarcassonneCentral

I also reccomend using the Host - Workshop menu to load the mods you want into your game, as opposed to saving them to your chest.

ObjectStates.Description: More tiles for the Wells, but requires The Mountains, The Forest, and The Fishermen.

ContainedObjects.Nickname: Wells - The Fountain of Youth - By Meepleater

These do however require
The Mountain
The Forest
The Fishermen

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds 12 tiles with new variations to the base game

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description:
36 Variants of basic tiles.
Also has 1 tile for the River or The Fishermen.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Contains
Mathguy 89
Mathguy 2008
Mathguy Gamma.
36 tiles of variations requested by Mathguy, and made by Novelty

Also contains 1 tile with a river, which should be removed, unless you're playing with The Fishermen.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds The Fisherman expansion

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Makes rivers a placeable feature in game.
Follows the same basic rules as other features.

Placing a follower on a river works as normally, but only with normal, big, and phantom meeple.

Unfinished river at end of game: 1 point per tile
Finished river grants 2 points per tile.
Wagons can't be placed on the river, as they cannot swim.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds tiles for The Fishermen and The Forest, you should only use this if you're playing with both of them.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Fishermen - The Whispering Woods - By Novelty
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds 60 More tiles to The Fishermen, meant to be used alongside The Fishermen and The Forest.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds the Mountains

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Mountains - By Novelty and Scott
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds Mountain tiles to the game.
You cannot place followers on them like with normal feature.
You instead get points when you place them, based on how many mountain edges they connect to.

Score card for how many point you get is inside the bag. I reccomend downloading the rule .pdf, if you have questions.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Mountains - By Novelty and Scott
ContainedObjects.Description:

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds tiles to the Mountains - with shrines and monasteries

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Mountains - High Places - By Novelty
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds more tiles to The Mountain. Some of them including Shrines or Cloisters.
( Cloisters function like a Monastery. )

You cannot deploy farmers on a field if it' doesn't have a field on one of the edges.
( There are some tiles with farms only in the middle, not on the edge, in this pack. )

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Nickname: Medium - The Mountains - The Dragon's Lair
ObjectStates.Description: Adds tiles for The Mountains + Princess and Dragon

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Small expansion to The Mountains, adds 27 tiles.
Some of them have the icons from The Princess and The Dragon.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: Adds a giant 150-tile expansion, adding forests to the game. not to be mixed up with " The Little Forest."

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Forests - By Scott and Novelty
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds a massive, 150 tile expansion based around adding forests to Carcassonne.

You can place followers on them as per the basic rules.Finished forests grant 1 point per tile.
Unfinished forests grant 1 point at the end of the game.

Followers can only be placed on forest edges, not corners/thin strips in the middle of the tile.

ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: A sequel to The Forest, adding 60 more tiles, but no new mechanics/rules

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: The Forests - Green Dragon  By Novelty and Scott
ContainedObjects.Description:
Expansion/Sequel to the Forests. Adds 60 additional tiles.

Also adds a Logging camp.
(Small  camp in a 4-sided forest tile. )
That grants 2 points per finished forest tile, instead of 1. ( +1 per tile )
Otherwise the tiles in the forest are worth 0.

Functions like the Cathedral for cities.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds more tiles with many icons from various offical and unofficial expansions

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds the Merry Men to the game, allowing players to make brawling champions that increase the value of a forest.

In addition it adds the Outlaw, a card that grants the player that has completed the largest forest bonus points based on how many forests there are on the map.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description:
Give this to the player that has completed the largest forest.
( Or has a follower with a green apple, from "An Apple a Day. )

Grants 1 point per completed forest at the end of the game to the player.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: Forests : Merry Men - By Novelty p2
ContainedObjects.Description:
Rules part 4:
When completing a forest with a Brawling champion, the brawling champion gets 2 points per forest tile, and then removes all their followers.
The Forest is then scored normally, for the other players in it.
For an incomplete forest, the Brawling Champion gets 1 point per forest tile, other players get 0.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: Forests : Merry Men - By Novelty p3
ContainedObjects.Description:
Rules part 3:
In a forest with a brawling champion, everyone in the forest is competing for the title.

Any player with a majority of woodsmen in a forest will take over as Brawling Champion, and is free to switch one of the followers in the forest with the follower in the merry men camp.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: Forests : Merry Men - By Novelty p2
ContainedObjects.Description:
Rules part 2:
If a follower is not placed on the camp, it will be inactive for the rest of the game.
But if a follower is placed on it, that follower will be a Brawling champion!

The Player with a Brawling Champion will gain 2 points per forest tile, instead of 1.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Rules:
The Oulaw is given to the player that completes the largest forest. At the end of the game, the player with the Outlaw gains 1 point per completed forest on the map.

There is a Merry Men Camp. ( Small round encampment surrounded by forest. ) added.
When a player places this, they can choose to place a follower on the forest, or the camp.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds more tiles to the Forest, in addition to The Oulaw Tiles, which grants extra points to the player with the largest forest, based on how many forests there are at the end of the game.

Downloading the pdf is highly reccomended. 
http://www.carcassonnecentral.com/community/index.php?action=downloads;sa=view;down=46

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds Magic Apples, as well as Apple Trade tokens to the game.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Contains the apple tokens, for Forests: An Apple a Day

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Place under a woodsman ( Follower in a Forest ) And the owner of the follower will get the Outlaw Tile. ( Requires Forests: Merry Men. ) The Outlaw will remain in the possesion of the player for as long as the green apple is under a woodsman. ( This overrides giving it to the player who has completed the largest forest. )

It is removed on scoring the forest+removing the woodsman.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Place under a follower to grant the follower's owner an extra tile-placement their next round.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Place under a follower to make them immune to being forcibly moved. ( Immune to Tower, Dragon. Remove again when removing the follower, on scoring the feature. )

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Can be placed under any follower, and gives them +1 strength for determining how many followers are on a feature. ( ex. a follower will count as if it were a big follower, and a big follower as if it were 3 normal sized followers. )

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
May be placed under any follower, and will make it so that they don't count for determining how many followers are on a feature. 

( It just straight up incapacitates a follower, until it's removed on scoring. making the follower useless. )

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description:
Palce this under any follower, once that follower is moved for any reason. ( Dragon, scoring a feature and returning the follower, or even the tower ) Then the owner may trade this token for a trade token from another player, the other player cannot refuse.

( aka you just pick a trade token someone else has, and take it, and give this in return. )

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Place under a follower to grant the follower's owner an extra tile-placement their next round.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: Just a normal Tradegood

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: An Apple a Day -  Cappy p3
ContainedObjects.Description:
You can place Apples under followers on any turn you haven't placed followers yourself.

The normal Red Apples work as normal trade tokens.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: An Apple a Day -  Cappy p2
ContainedObjects.Description:
If you place a tile with an apple on bordering another tile with an apple on, you are allowed to take 2 apple tokens from the bag.

If it borders 3, you are allowed to take 3.

Most apples are removed from play after they've been used.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
I highly reccomend downloading the rule pdf.
@ http://www.carcassonnecentral.com/community/index.php?action=downloads;sa=view;down=49

But I will try to summarize the rules.
When you place a tile with an apple token on, you get to immediately withdraw an Apple token from the bag.
                                                                  page1

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Model
ContainedObjects.Description:
Huffs. Puffs.

Once it's on the field, any player can make it move 1 tile instead of placing a follower.

It cannot move diagonally, nor can it cross holes, jump, or cross over to other features than the type it's currently on.

When placed for the first time, the player placing the tile can move it once for free.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Wolf Rules part 2

Wolves eat followers, and return them to their owner.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Wolf rules!
1: when a tile with a wolf icon is placed, the wolf is to be placed on that icon, on the feature the icon is on. (They can place a follower afterwards.)
2: The player placing it may choose to move it 1 tile. ( It cannot move diagonally, or cross over or onto other features. )
3: Any player can choose to move it 1 tile instead of placing a follower their turn.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds 12 tiles to the Forests, based on fairy tales. Also adds the big bad wolf!

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds a 1-tile disaster to Forests, removing all value.

ContainedObjects.Name: Card
ContainedObjects.Description: FIREEEEEE

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: Forests : Forest Fire - By JPutty927 - p2
ContainedObjects.Description:
Players can remove their woodsmen by either completing the forest, or by adding a tile to it as normal, and choosing to remove their woodmen instead of placing a follower that turn.

Players are allowed to remove all their woodsmen from the forest in the same turn.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds 1 tile, the Forest Fire.
Adding this to a forest removes the value from all of it's tiles.
Logging camps will provide 0 points.
The extra-turn cherries will not provide extra turns when placed.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds Log Cabins / Hunter lodges to the games, as a variant of the monastery for Forests.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds Log Cabins.
1: When placing a log cabin, you can place a follower as usual, or onto the cabin as a hunter.
2: The cabin is complete when all 4 corner. ( corner, not sides) are complete.
3: A finished cabin grants 7 points, plus 2 points per forest tile in the corners.
( Thus, 7 - 15 points. )

Corners, as in tiles diagonally from the cabin.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds Timber/Wood as a trade resouce for forests

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You should probably copy a couple of these.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Nickname: Forests : Timber - By Scott and Novelty
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds Forest tiles with Timber Trade Tokens, adding a new trade resource to the game.

ContainedObjects.Name: Bag
ContainedObjects.Description: Adds 3 new icons to the Forests, adding tiles that grant extra points, or extra turns to the tiles.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Icon 3: Woodman's Guild ( Acorn. )
Grants +1 point on the tile. For both completed and incomplete forests.

( Unless said forest has burned down. )

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds 3 new icons to forest tiles.
1: Cherries:
If a cherry tile is placed in a forest where a player has a woodsman, they are granted an extra turn.
2: Chivalry ( Red and yellow icon. )
If the player places it in a forest where they already have a follower, they are allowed to swap that follower with one from their hand,
Or they can place a follower normally.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Token
ContainedObjects.Description: You can keep me, and try to have the most at the end of the game, or you can sell me when you get me instead, for 3 points.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
About the Ore tokens:
When a player gets an Ore Trade Token from completing a mountain range, by having miners there. They can opt to sell it instead of keeping it, granting them 3 points immediately.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Adds Mines to mountains.
When placing a mountain tile with an ore icon on it, the player can place a follower on it to become a miner.
If the tile with the ore icon on it extends an existing mountain, the player placing it can get an extra turn.

When the mountain is finished, the player will get a trade token from the miner.
